sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M45750
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Codes for the Hd1a protein which blocks sodium channels, specifically Nav1.1 and Nav1.7, and can be used as an analgesic. A 10x histidine has been included for purification, and an enterokinase protease site has been included to cleave off the histidine tag after purification.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Alex Torgesen
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: It is peptide μ-TRTX-Hd1a from the venom of Haplopelma doriae.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This part has been optimized for use in E. coli.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0015
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Double terminator consisting of BBa_B0010 and BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcriptional terminator consisting of a 64 bp stem-loop.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Randy Rettberg

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M45711
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Hd1a toxin from Haplopelma doriae spider
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Hd1a shows signs of being possibly used as another analgesic. It effectively blocks the Nav1.7 sodium channel and thus is an effective pain blocker.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Nicholas D. Lauritzen
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance:
This sequence comes from the Haplopelma doriae spider.
http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1111/bph.13081/full
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This sequence has been codon optimized for RC 10.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M45751
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the recognition site for enterokinase which cleaves after the lysine leaving no residual amino acids.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Alex Torgesen
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: It comes from the intestines where enterokinase recognizes the site and cuts trypsinogen into its active form of trypsin.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Optimized for use in E. coli.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1162009
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: 10x-Histidine (10x-His) Tag with Met (ATG) For N-terminal purification
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part uses assembly standard 23 (RFC 23-silver fusion) to allow for protein fusions. This 10x His Tag is similar to BBa_K844000 but has the double stop codon (TAA TAA) removed unlike BBa_K844000. (http://parts.igem.org/wiki/index.php?title=Part:BBa_K844000). Another characteristic of this part is the presence of a Met (ATG) for direct His Tag and protein expression. Since the presence of the Met (ATG) this His Tag should be used for protein purification at the N-terminal. The user can place a promoter-rbs system of their choice in front of this His Tag for direct expression. The lack of any stop codon in this His Tag allows the user to add additional features downstream of the gene e.g. secretion tag or GFP (note, the gene itself must not contain any stop codons if the His Tag is to be used like this). Related parts BBa_K844000 (http://parts.igem.org/wiki/index.php?title=Part:BBa_K844000), this link also provides an extensive review of existing Histidine Tags in the Parts Registry.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Kathleen Miller
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: RFC 23 and contains an atg (met). No stop codon.
